cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the generalization performance of deep learning models, specifically linear classifiers with convolutional layers. This topic falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the generalization bias of deep learning models, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV and cs.NE.
